<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>HIST 1760 — Midterm Review</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;700;900&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@300;400;500&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0e0e0e; --surface: #161616; --card: #1e1e1e; --border: #2e2e2e;
    --gold: #c9a84c; --gold-dim: #7a6230; --text: #e8e0d0; --text-dim: #888;
    --red: #c0392b; --green: #2ecc71; --cn-bg: #111a0e; --cn-border: #2a3a20; --cn-text: #a8c898; --cn-label: #5a8a3a;
  }
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif; min-height: 100vh; }
  header { padding: 48px 40px 32px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; }
  .header-title { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 48px); font-weight: 900; color: var(--gold); line-height: 1; }
  .header-sub { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-top: 8px; }
  nav { display: flex; padding: 0 40px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--surface); }
  .tab { padding: 16px 28px; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-dim); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; transition: all 0.2s; background: none; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; }
  .tab:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .tab.active { color: var(--gold); border-bottom-color: var(--gold); }
  main { padding: 40px; max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .panel { display: none; }
  .panel.active { display: block; }
  .filter-bar { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 32px; align-items: center; }
  .filter-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-right: 4px; }
  .filter-btn { padding: 6px 14px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: none; color: var(--text-dim); font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 2px; transition: all 0.15s; }
  .filter-btn:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); color: var(--text); }
  .filter-btn.active { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--gold); background: rgba(201,168,76,0.08); }
  .keywords-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(360px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; }
  .keyword-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 24px; transition: border-color 0.2s; }
  .keyword-card:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); }
  .kw-group-tag { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-dim); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .kw-title { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .kw-section-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold-dim); margin-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 12px; }
  .kw-text { font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.65; color: #c8c0b0; }
  /* CN TOGGLE */
  .cn-toggle { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-top: 16px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
  .cn-toggle-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--cn-label); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .cn-toggle:hover .cn-toggle-label { color: #7ab85a; }
  .cn-arrow { font-size: 9px; color: var(--cn-label); transition: transform 0.2s; display: inline-block; }
  .cn-arrow.open { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  .cn-block { display: none; margin-top: 10px; background: var(--cn-bg); border: 1px solid var(--cn-border); border-radius: 3px; padding: 14px 16px; }
  .cn-block.open { display: block; }
  .cn-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--cn-label); margin-bottom: 3px; margin-top: 10px; }
  .cn-label:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
  .cn-text { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--cn-text); }
  /* FLASHCARDS */
  .flashcard-controls { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .fc-counter { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-dim); min-width: 80px; }
  .fc-progress { flex: 1; height: 2px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; min-width: 100px; }
  .fc-progress-fill { height: 100%; background: var(--gold); border-radius: 2px; transition: width 0.3s; }
  .btn { padding: 10px 22px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: none; color: var(--text); font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 2px; transition: all 0.15s; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .btn:hover { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--gold); }
  .btn.primary { background: var(--gold); color: #0e0e0e; border-color: var(--gold); font-weight: 500; }
  .btn.primary:hover { background: #d4a94f; }
  .fc-scene { perspective: 1200px; width: 100%; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto 32px; height: 380px; cursor: pointer; }
  .fc-card { width: 100%; height: 100%; position: relative; transform-style: preserve-3d; transition: transform 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.23,1,0.32,1); }
  .fc-card.flipped { transform: rotateY(180deg); }
  .fc-face { position: absolute; width: 100%; height: 100%; backface-visibility: hidden; border-radius: 6px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 40px; text-align: center; }
  .fc-front { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .fc-back { background: #1a1a14; border: 1px solid var(--gold-dim); transform: rotateY(180deg); justify-content: flex-start; align-items: flex-start; text-align: left; overflow-y: auto; padding: 28px 32px; }
  .fc-front-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .fc-front-term { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: clamp(22px,4vw,34px); font-weight: 700; color: var(--gold); line-height: 1.2; }
  .fc-front-hint { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-top: 20px; }
  .fc-back-title { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 18px; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 700; }
  .fc-back-row { margin-bottom: 7px; font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.55; color: #c8c0b0; }
  .fc-back-row strong { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold-dim); display: block; margin-bottom: 1px; }
  .fc-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--cn-border); margin: 10px 0; }
  .fc-cn-row { margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--cn-text); }
  .fc-cn-row strong { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--cn-label); display: block; margin-bottom: 1px; }
  .fc-result-btns { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 12px; margin-top: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-know { border-color: var(--green); color: var(--green); }
  .btn-know:hover { background: rgba(46,204,113,0.1); }
  .btn-review { border-color: var(--red); color: #e74c3c; }
  .btn-review:hover { background: rgba(192,57,43,0.1); }
  .score-bar { display: flex; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 24px; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .score-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
  .score-dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .dot-know { background: var(--green); } .dot-review { background: var(--red); } .dot-unseen { background: var(--border); }
  .fc-filter { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 24px; align-items: center; }
  .fc-nav { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  @media (max-width:600px) { header { padding: 28px 20px 20px; } nav { padding: 0 8px; overflow-x: auto; } main { padding: 24px 16px; } .tab { padding: 14px 16px; font-size: 11px; } }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <div>
    <div class="header-title">African History — Midterm Review</div>
    <div class="header-sub">HIST 1760 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Prof. Abosede George &nbsp;·&nbsp; 30 Keywords</div>
  </div>
</header>
<nav>
  <button class="tab active" onclick="switchTab('keywords')">Keywords</button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="switchTab('flashcards')">Flashcards</button>
</nav>
<main>
  <div class="panel active" id="panel-keywords">
    <div class="filter-bar">
      <span class="filter-label">Filter:</span>
      <button class="filter-btn active" onclick="filterGroup('all',this)">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('1',this)">Group 1</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('2',this)">Group 2</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('3',this)">Group 3</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('4',this)">Group 4</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('5',this)">Group 5</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('6',this)">Group 6</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('7',this)">Group 7</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('8',this)">Group 8</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('9',this)">Group 9</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterGroup('10',this)">Group 10</button>
    </div>
    <div class="keywords-grid" id="keywords-grid"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel" id="panel-flashcards">
    <div class="fc-filter">
      <span class="filter-label">Deck:</span>
      <button class="filter-btn active" onclick="fcFilter('all',this)">All 30</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="fcFilter('review',this)">Needs Review</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" onclick="fcFilter('unseen',this)">Unseen Only</button>
    </div>
    <div class="score-bar">
      <div class="score-item"><div class="score-dot dot-know"></div><span id="score-know">0 know</span></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="score-dot dot-review"></div><span id="score-review">0 review</span></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="score-dot dot-unseen"></div><span id="score-unseen">30 unseen</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="flashcard-controls">
      <span class="fc-counter" id="fc-counter">1 / 30</span>
      <div class="fc-progress"><div class="fc-progress-fill" id="fc-progress" style="width:0%"></div></div>
      <button class="btn" onclick="shuffleDeck()">Shuffle</button>
      <button class="btn primary" onclick="resetDeck()">Reset</button>
    </div>
    <div class="fc-scene" onclick="flipCard()">
      <div class="fc-card" id="fc-card">
        <div class="fc-face fc-front">
          <div class="fc-front-label">Term</div>
          <div class="fc-front-term" id="fc-term"></div>
          <div class="fc-front-hint">click to reveal</div>
        </div>
        <div class="fc-face fc-back" id="fc-back-content"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fc-result-btns" id="fc-result-btns" style="display:none">
      <button class="btn btn-know" onclick="markCard('know')">✓ Got it</button>
      <button class="btn btn-review" onclick="markCard('review')">↺ Review again</button>
    </div>
    <div class="fc-nav">
      <button class="btn" onclick="fcNav(-1)">← Prev</button>
      <button class="btn" onclick="fcNav(1)">Next →</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
<script>
const KW = [
  { g:'1', term:'Sundiata',
    who:'Sundiata Keita — founder and first Mansa (king) of the Mali Empire',
    what:'Legendary warrior-king who united Mande peoples, defeated the Sosso kingdom, and established the Mali Empire. Central figure in the Epic of Sundiata (oral history).',
    where:'West Africa — Mali Empire, centered on the upper Niger River',
    when:'c. 1217–1255 CE',
    sig:'Founded the largest West African empire of its era. Expanded trans-Saharan trade. The Epic of Sundiata illustrates African statecraft and history-keeping outside written records.',
    cwho:'松迪亚塔·凯塔——马里帝国的创始人兼首任曼萨（国王）',
    cwhat:'传奇战士国王，统一曼德族群，击败索索王国，建立马里帝国。《松迪亚塔史诗》的核心人物。',
    cwhere:'西非——马里帝国，以尼日尔河上游为中心',
    cwhen:'约公元1217–1255年',
    csig:'建立了那个时代西非最大的帝国，扩大了跨撒哈拉贸易联系。《松迪亚塔史诗》是非洲口述传统的重要代表，展示了文字记录之外的非洲国家治理与历史传承方式。'
  },
  { g:'1', term:'Songhay (Empire)',
    who:'Sunni Ali (r. 1462–1492) and Askia Muhammad (r. 1493–1538) — key rulers',
    what:'The largest West African empire of the 15th–16th centuries, rising from Gao after Mali\'s decline. Controlled gold and salt routes; Askia Muhammad promoted Islam and made a pilgrimage to Mecca.',
    where:'West Africa — centered on Gao along the Niger River, spanning the Sahel',
    when:'1464–1591 CE',
    sig:'Height of Sudanic empire building. Fell to a Moroccan invasion (1591), illustrating African states\' vulnerability to firearms-equipped external forces.',
    cwho:'桑尼·阿里（在位1462–1492年）和阿斯基亚·穆罕默德（在位1493–1538年）',
    cwhat:'15至16世纪西非最强大的帝国，在马里帝国衰落后从加奥城崛起，控制黄金和盐的贸易路线。阿斯基亚·穆罕默德推广伊斯兰教并朝觐麦加。',
    cwhere:'西非——以尼日尔河沿岸的加奥为中心，横跨萨赫勒地区',
    cwhen:'公元1464–1591年',
    csig:'代表了苏丹帝国建设的巅峰。1591年被摩洛哥入侵所灭，揭示了非洲国家面对配备火器的外部势力时的脆弱性。'
  },
  { g:'1', term:'Trans-Saharan Trade',
    who:'West African kingdoms (Mali, Songhay), North African merchants, Arab traders, Berber caravaneers',
    what:'North-south commercial network across the Sahara. West Africa exported gold, enslaved people, kola nuts; North Africa exported textiles, horses, glass, and Islam.',
    where:'Sahara Desert — connecting West African Sahel to the Mediterranean coast',
    when:'c. 400–1700 CE; peak during medieval Sudanic empires',
    sig:'Drove the rise of West African empires. Facilitated the spread of Islam. Sent nearly 5 million enslaved people northward (650–1600 CE). Introduction of camels (300–400 CE) was the key technological enabler.',
    cwho:'西非王国（马里、桑海）、北非商人、阿拉伯贸易商、柏柏尔商队',
    cwhat:'穿越撒哈拉的南北商业网络。西非出口黄金、被奴役者、可乐果；北非出口纺织品、马匹、玻璃及伊斯兰教。',
    cwhere:'撒哈拉沙漠——连接西非萨赫勒地区与地中海沿岸',
    cwhen:'约公元400–1700年；中世纪苏丹帝国时期达到顶峰',
    csig:'推动了西非帝国的兴起，促进了伊斯兰教在西非的传播。公元650–1600年间约有500万被奴役者被贩往北方。骆驼的引入（约公元300–400年）是关键技术推动因素。'
  },
  { g:'2', term:'Axum (Aksum)',
    who:'Aksumite rulers, notably King Ezana (converted to Christianity c. 340 CE)',
    what:'One of the earliest and most powerful East African kingdoms. Exported gold, ivory, and enslaved people via the Red Sea. Adopted Christianity as state religion c. 340 CE.',
    where:'Horn of Africa — present-day northern Ethiopia and Eritrea',
    when:'1st–9th century CE',
    sig:'Proto-foundation of the Ethiopian empire and Solomonic dynasty. Ethiopia\'s Eastern Orthodox Christianity made it a unique African Christian civilization independent of European control.',
    cwho:'阿克苏姆统治者，尤其是埃扎纳国王（约公元340年皈依基督教）',
    cwhat:'东非最早也最强大的王国之一。通过红海出口黄金、象牙和被奴役者。约公元340年将基督教定为国教。',
    cwhere:'非洲之角——今埃塞俄比亚北部和厄立特里亚',
    cwhen:'公元1至9世纪',
    csig:'埃塞俄比亚帝国与所罗门王朝的雏形。东正教基督教使其成为独立于欧洲控制之外的独特非洲基督教文明。'
  },
  { g:'2', term:'Zamana Masafent',
    who:'Regional warlords (Ras), Emperor Iyoas I, Mikael Sehul, Emperor Tewodros II',
    what:'"Era of the Princes" — political fragmentation in Ethiopia where the Solomonic emperor became a figurehead while regional lords competed for power. Emperors were repeatedly deposed and reinstated.',
    where:'Ethiopia — centered in Gondar',
    when:'1769–1855 CE',
    sig:'Represents a recurring pattern of centralization-fragmentation in African political history. Ended when Emperor Tewodros II forcibly reunified Ethiopia.',
    cwho:'地方军阀（拉斯）、伊约阿斯一世皇帝、米卡埃尔·赛胡尔、特沃德罗斯二世皇帝',
    cwhat:'"王公时代"——埃塞俄比亚政治分裂时期，所罗门王朝皇帝沦为傀儡，地方领主争夺权力。皇帝屡遭废黜又反复复位。',
    cwhere:'埃塞俄比亚——以贡德尔为中心',
    cwhen:'公元1769–1855年',
    csig:'体现了非洲政治史中中央集权与分裂割据反复交替的规律。特沃德罗斯二世皇帝强行统一埃塞俄比亚后这一时期告终。'
  },
  { g:'2', term:'Solomonic Lineage',
    who:'Ethiopian emperors claiming descent from King Solomon and the Queen of Sheba via their son Menelik I',
    what:'Ideological claim of divine-royal legitimacy, codified in the Kebra Nagast ("Glory of Kings"). Every emperor claimed Solomonic descent. Title: Negusa Nagast ("King of Kings").',
    where:'Ethiopia — Horn of Africa',
    when:'13th century CE revival onwards; claim traces to ancient Axum',
    sig:'Provided the ideological backbone of Ethiopian imperial rule for centuries. Justified resistance to colonization as defense of a divinely ordained Christian kingdom. Underpinned Menelik II\'s authority at Adwa.',
    cwho:'埃塞俄比亚历代皇帝，自称通过所罗门王与示巴女王之子孟尼利克一世传承血脉',
    cwhat:'神圣王权合法性的意识形态主张，载于《荣耀之书》（Kebra Nagast）。每位皇帝均声称拥有所罗门血统。头衔：内古斯·内加斯特（"万王之王"）。',
    cwhere:'埃塞俄比亚——非洲之角',
    cwhen:'公元13世纪王朝复兴起；追溯至古代阿克苏姆',
    csig:'数百年来为埃塞俄比亚帝国统治提供意识形态支柱。将抵抗殖民主义诠释为捍卫神圣基督教王国，为孟尼利克二世在阿杜瓦战役中的权威提供合法性基础。'
  },
  { g:'3', term:'"Islamic" Slavery Model',
    who:'Islamic states, merchants, and households across North Africa, the Middle East, and East Africa',
    what:'A slavery system connected to trans-Saharan and Indian Ocean trade networks. Used for domestic labor, military service (e.g., Mamluks), and agriculture. Key distinction: not strictly hereditary or racialized.',
    where:'Sahara, Red Sea, Indian Ocean, East Africa, Middle East, South Asia',
    when:'7th century CE onwards',
    sig:'Predated and differed fundamentally from Atlantic slavery. Its relative fluidity contrasts with Atlantic chattel slavery\'s rigid racial hierarchy. Connected Africa to global trade networks centuries before European contact.',
    cwho:'北非、中东和东非的伊斯兰国家、商人及家庭',
    cwhat:'与跨撒哈拉和印度洋贸易网络相连的奴役制度。用于家务劳动、军事服务（如马穆鲁克）和农业。关键区别：并非严格意义上的世袭制，也没有明显的种族化特征。',
    cwhere:'撒哈拉、红海、印度洋、东非、中东、南亚',
    cwhen:'公元7世纪起',
    csig:'早于大西洋奴隶制且与其本质不同。其相对灵活性与大西洋动产奴隶制的严格种族等级制度形成鲜明对比。在欧洲接触非洲的数百年前便将非洲纳入全球贸易网络。'
  },
  { g:'3', term:'Three Phases of the Atlantic Slave Trade',
    who:'Phase I: Portugal, Spain. Phase II: Britain, France, Netherlands. Phase III: abolitionist movements vs. illegal traders',
    what:'Phase I (15th–16th c.): Early Iberian trade routes. Phase II (17th–18th c.): Massive expansion; plantation slavery drives demand. Phase III (19th c.): Britain bans trade (1807); illegal trade continues.',
    where:'Atlantic basin — West and Central Africa to the Americas',
    when:'15th–19th centuries',
    sig:'Caused massive demographic loss in Africa. Funded early European capitalism. The shift from Phase II to III shows how abolitionism did not immediately end the trade, revealing its deep economic entrenchment.',
